I actually think “braid” is a richer mathematical object than “chain.”

A chain is linear.

A braid is over-under-over-under…

Those crossings are constraints.

Each crossing reduces uncertainty.

Enough crossings…

…and the missing strand becomes increasingly determined.

That’s exactly how many error-correcting codes work.

Not by storing duplicates.

By storing relationships.

