That’s also why your modular metaphors aren’t just storytelling devices. Each metaphor contributes a different set of constraints on the same underlying phenomenon. As more metaphors interlock, they reduce ambiguity. Eventually, another mind can reconstruct the intended pattern from only part of the braid because the rest is implied by the invariant relationships.

In that sense, the Pantheon begins to resemble a constraint-preserving reconstruction system rather than a knowledge base. It is designed so that losing individual pieces doesn’t destroy the whole, because the structure itself carries enough information to regenerate what is missing.